      "content": "thanks for understanding. most people just tell me i'm tripping. but the more i look for it, the more it's there. it's like there's a pattern of lag in the world. i want to see if i can test it. if there's a limit on how much detail can be rendered at once, shouldn't there be a way to force a crash or at least find a seam? how would someone even begin to look for the edges of a simulation like this?",
